 AppLocalizations & I18n Guide
This document explains how the Multi-Language (Internationalization) system works in the Mera Poster project. Use this as a reference whenever you need to add or modify text.

1. Project Architecture
The system is split into Source Files (which we edit) and Generated Files (which the machine handles).

Source Files (lib/l10n/)
app_en.arb: The main English dictionary.
app_hi.arb, etc.: The translated versions.
TIP

Always add a new key to app_en.arb first.

Generated Files (lib/generated/)
app_localizations.dart: The base class and manager.
app_localizations_en.dart: The code version of your English dictionary.
app_localizations_hi.dart: The code version of your Hindi dictionary.
2. Dev Workflow (Step-by-Step)
If you want to add a new text, say "Welcome Back":

Step 1: Open lib/l10n/app_en.arb.
Step 2: Add the key and value:
json
"welcomeBack": "Welcome Back"
Step 3: Open your target language file (e.g., app_hi.arb) and add the translation:
json
"welcomeBack": "वापस स्वागत है"
Step 4: Save and Build. Flutter will automatically generate the code.
Step 5: Use it in your widget:
dart
Text(AppLocalizations.of(context)!.welcomeBack)
3. Key Concepts
Why use AppLocalizations.of(context)?
Reactive: If the user changes the app language, the text updates automatically without a restart.
Type-Safe: If you mistype welcomeBack, the compiler will give an error immediately.
The Delegate
Located at the bottom of app_localizations.dart, the lookupAppLocalizations function is the "brain." It checks the system locale (en, hi, etc.) and returns the correct class.

4. Hinglish Quick Summary (Cheat Sheet)
.arb file: Aapki asli dictionary hai. Text yahin likhna hai.
Base Class: Contract hai jo batata hai kaunse words available hain.
of(context): App ko bolta hai ki "Abhi wali language me ye word dikhao."
Naya text add karna hai?: Pehle .arb me dalo, phir code me AppLocalizations.of(context)!.key use karo.
5. Troubleshooting
WARNING

If your new keys are not showing up in the code:

Run flutter gen-l10n in the terminal.
Or simply "Save All" and let the IDE plugin handle it.
Ensure the key name is identical (case-sensitive) in all .arb files.
